---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="The Automations Guide covers automation tools and workflows for RevOps and GTM teams."
>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="about-hero">
      <p class="section-label">About this site</p>
      <h1>We write about automation so your team doesn't have to figure it out the hard way.</h1>
      <p style="color:var(--text-muted);font-size:1.0625rem;line-height:1.75;max-width:580px;margin-top:1rem;">
        The Automations Guide is an independent publication covering automation tools,
        RevOps workflows, and GTM strategy. We cut through the vendor noise and share
        what actually works.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="about-content">
      <div class="prose">
        <h2>What we cover</h2>
        <p>
          Revenue Operations is increasingly defined by the quality of the automation layer
          underneath it. Broken handoffs, manual data entry, and disconnected tools cost
          pipeline and erode team trust.
        </p>
        <p>
          This site exists to help RevOps practitioners, GTM leaders, and ops-minded
          founders build automation stacks that actually hold up — from the first Zap to
          a full-scale HubSpot orchestration.
        </p>

        <h3>Topics we dig into</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Automation platform comparisons (Zapier, Make, n8n, and beyond)</li>
          <li>HubSpot, Salesforce, and CRM workflow automation</li>
          <li>Sales &amp; marketing handoff automation</li>
          <li>Lead routing, scoring, and enrichment workflows</li>
          <li>RevOps tech stack design and tooling decisions</li>
          <li>AI-powered automation in GTM contexts</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How we work</h2>
        <p>
          Every article is written from hands-on experience. We test the tools we write
          about, document what breaks, and share the real tradeoffs — not just the
          marketing pitch.
        </p>
        <p>
          Some links on this site are affiliate links. When you click through and purchase
          a tool we recommend, we may earn a small commission. This never influences our
          editorial take — we only recommend tools we'd use ourselves.
        </p>

        <h2>Affiliate Disclosure</h2>
        <p>
          The Automations Guide participates in affiliate programs with several of the
          tools we cover. This means we may receive compensation when you sign up for or
          purchase a product through a link on this site. We are committed to full
          transparency: affiliate relationships are disclosed on relevant pages, and our
          editorial recommendations are based on genuine evaluation — not commission size.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
